Determine the required classroom dimensions to comfortably fit 16 student desks (4x4), a teacher desk, aisles, and other objects. 2. Create 16 student desks arranged in 4 rows of 4 desks each, each paired with a matching chair, ensuring clear walkways between rows. 3. Create a larger teacher’s desk centered at the front of the room, facing student desks. 4. Add a large rectangular blackboard mounted on the front wall above the teacher’s desk. 5. Create a ceiling-mounted projector aligned with the blackboard. 6. Add two tall bookshelves filled with books, positioned along the left and right side walls. 7. Place a round wall clock on the right side wall at a height visible from any desk. 8. Create two potted plants in the front-left and front-right corners of the room. 9. Design and place 12 ceiling lights in a 4×3 grid overhead. 10. Add six educational posters evenly spaced on side and back walls. 11. Place two waste bins: one near the teacher’s desk, one at the back wall. 12. Create a large window with curtains on the back wall for natural light. 13. Ensure all student chairs face toward the front wall. 14. Provide ample walking space between desks, aisles, and other objects. 15. Color student desks medium wood tone, teacher desk darker wood tone, chairs soft blue; walls white; floor tiles light gray. 16. Determine the required classroom dimensions to comfortably fit 16 student desks (4x4), a teacher desk, aisles, and other objects. 2. Create 16 student desks arranged in 4 rows of 4 desks each, each paired with a matching chair, ensuring clear walkways between rows. 3. Create a larger teacher’s desk centered at the front of the room, facing student desks. 4. Add a large rectangular blackboard mounted on the front wall above the teacher’s desk. 5. Create a ceiling-mounted projector aligned with the blackboard. 6. Add two tall bookshelves filled with books, positioned along the left and right side walls. 7. Place a round wall clock on the right side wall at a height visible from any desk. 8. Create two potted plants in the front-left and front-right corners of the room. 9. Design and place 12 ceiling lights in a 4×3 grid overhead. 10. Add six educational posters evenly spaced on side and back walls. 11. Place two waste bins: one near the teacher’s desk, one at the back wall. 12. Create a large window with curtains on the back wall for natural light. 13. Ensure all student chairs face toward the front wall. 14. Provide ample walking space between desks, aisles, and other objects. 15. Color student desks medium wood tone, teacher desk darker wood tone, chairs soft blue; walls white; floor tiles light gray. 16. Create a floor sized to encompass all objects and walkways (8m × 10m). 17. Create four walls (front, back, left, right) to enclose the classroom. 18. Place objects either on the floor, mounted on walls, or ceiling as appropriate.\n\n            Use these relations for the objects: [\'floor | middle | ground\', \'front_wall | front | edge\',
